and, well, I don't like it.

222
00:11:33,458 --> 00:11:36,125
Oh, I don't blame you.
A healthy relationship
should be a partnership.

223
00:11:36,125 --> 00:11:39,000
Well, it's never really equal.
Someone always ends up on top.

224
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,250
Yeah, but you know,
sometimes it's okay
to switch.

225
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:43,291
-Really?
-Mm, down the line.

226
00:11:43,291 --> 00:11:45,792
I think I hear
what you guys are saying.

227
00:11:45,792 --> 00:11:49,375
I'm the man,
and I have to reclaim
the power in my marriage.

228
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,208
Hey, thanks, fellas.

229
00:11:53,542 --> 00:11:57,709
-Take a picture, why don't you?
-I'm just being polite.
It'd be rude not to look.

230
00:11:59,166 --> 00:12:00,750
Forgive me, Francine.

231
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:03,041
I'm only doing this
to save our marriage.

232
00:12:05,792 --> 00:12:09,625
What am I thinking?
This is the woman I love.

233
00:12:09,625 --> 00:12:13,959
That's better.
Oh, damn it!
I'm such a softy.

234
00:12:13,959 --> 00:12:16,709
There's gotta be a better way
to put her out of business.

235
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:21,542
-Uh, excuse me,
are you Francine's boss?
-Yes.

236
00:12:21,542 --> 00:12:23,709
Go! Go! Go!

237
00:12:23,709 --> 00:12:25,834
-You're all under arrest.
-For what?

238
00:12:25,834 --> 00:12:28,542
-Possession
of cocaine doughnuts.
-Those are powdered sugar.

239
00:12:28,542 --> 00:12:32,375
Put it in a rap song,
jailbird. This office
is permanently closed.

240
00:12:32,375 --> 00:12:35,458
-What are you saying?
-I'm saying you're fired.

241
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:38,417
-(clears throat)
-Oh, for God's sake,
somebody pay Mr. Trump.

242
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:43,458
So you're sure
we can use this house
for our video shoot?

243
00:12:43,458 --> 00:12:46,959
I overheard my mom say
it's been on the market so long,
everybody's forgotten about it.

244
00:12:46,959 --> 00:12:50,750
Eavesdropper.
You should respect
her privacy.

245
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,875
You guys got beer, right?

246
00:12:52,875 --> 00:12:55,125
'Cause we're not going wild
and exposing our breasts
without beer.

247
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:58,375
-Gotcha covered.
-(Asian language)

248
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:02,417
What?

249
00:13:02,417 --> 00:13:06,125
We are going neither wild
nor totally wild
at a homeless shelter.

250
00:13:06,125 --> 00:13:08,667
But we are taking
your beer.

251
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:11,542
Hayley, you ruined everything.
What are you doing here?

252
00:13:11,542 --> 00:13:14,458
I'm giving these poor,
forgotten people
a new lease on life.

253
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:18,000
Um, Hayley,
I think Phil is dead.

254
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,083
(clamoring)

255
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:25,959
Now we'll never
get a Game Station.

256
00:13:25,959 --> 00:13:29,000
Au contraire,
my dear Snot.

257
00:13:31,041 --> 00:13:33,333
Hey, honey,
I just heard the news.

258
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:35,709
Too bad about your office
being closed down.

259
00:13:35,709 --> 00:13:37,917
Well, looks like I'm making
more money than you again.

260
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:40,208
I'd advise you to write
an offer soon, Randy.

261
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:42,500
Mortgage rates aren't going
to stay this low forever.

262
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:45,583
-That's real estate chatter.
-Silence, you fool.

263
00:13:45,583 --> 00:13:48,500
She's closing a duplex
at four percent over list.

264
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:51,458
Francine, what the hell
is going on?
You were fired.

265
00:13:51,458 --> 00:13:55,125
-That's passive past tense,
Trump. You don't own that.
-(growls)

266
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:57,917
Stan, I'm on the phone.
Sorry, Randy.

267
00:13:57,917 --> 00:14:00,417
I'm working out of
my home office these days.

268
00:14:00,417 --> 00:14:02,625
-Here you go, boss.
-Boss?

269
00:14:02,625 --> 00:14:05,750
I'm Miss Smith's assistant.
Can I get you something
while you wait?

270
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:08,875
-Uh, a bottled water.
-It's not cold.
Is that all right?

271
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:11,542
-Uh, forget it.
-(phone ringing)

272
00:14:11,542 --> 00:14:13,542
Fran Smith and Associate.

273
00:14:13,542 --> 00:14:16,583
Hold her calls.
Francine, I want you
to stop this nonsense.

274
00:14:16,583 --> 00:14:19,083
Nonsense?
This job is my career.

275
00:14:19,083 --> 00:14:22,542
No, my job is a career.
This is just some silly
housewife's hobby.

276
00:14:22,542 --> 00:14:26,125
Oh, yeah?
Well, this silly housewife
loves her hobby.

277
00:14:26,125 --> 00:14:29,125
She's good at it.
In fact, she kicks ass.

278
00:14:29,125 --> 00:14:31,458
So her big
career man husband

279
00:14:31,458 --> 00:14:34,125
-is just gonna have to
deal with it.
-I could have assassinated you.

280
00:14:34,125 --> 00:14:35,542
-What?
-Nothing.

281
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:41,458
-(sighs)
-HAYLEY: It was my house first.

282
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:43,792
You can't stand in the way
of progress, butt-face.

283
00:14:43,792 --> 00:14:45,542
Hey, hey,
what's going on here?

284
00:14:45,542 --> 00:14:47,458
Steve's making
the homeless men in my shelter

285
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:49,625
beat each other senseless.

286
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:52,750
It's called "Bum Fights."
I'm gonna make a fortune
selling tickets.

287
00:14:52,750 --> 00:14:56,875
It's exploitation.
You're making money
off their pain and misery.

288
00:14:56,875 --> 00:15:00,333
All right, Hayley,
I'll handle this.
Let me get this straight, Son.

289
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:02,792
You're pitting desperate,
downtrodden men
against one another

290
00:15:02,792 --> 00:15:04,750
in a violent confrontation
for profit?

291
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:07,417
-Yes, sir.
-I'm in.

292
00:15:14,542 --> 00:15:17,500
(gasps)

293
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:19,542
What the hell
is going on here?

294
00:15:19,542 --> 00:15:22,458
Ask Dad. He stole
my whole Bum Fights idea.

295
00:15:22,458 --> 00:15:24,500
He won't even give me
a piece of the action.

296
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:27,041
Okay, I want this
to be a class act.
I'll introduce you both,

297
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:29,333
you'll shake hands,
and then I'll throw
raw meat on the floor,

298
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:31,625
and whoever beats the crap
out of the other one
gets to eat.

299
00:15:31,625 --> 00:15:35,083
Dad, you were supposed
to shut this down. You're
degrading these poor men.

300
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:37,834
That's ridiculous.
I'm giving them jobs
and self-esteem.

301
00:15:37,834 --> 00:15:40,583
More importantly,
I'm giving them costumes
and a backstory.

302
00:15:40,583 --> 00:15:42,917
This is
The Garbage Collector.

303
00:15:42,917 --> 00:15:47,291
He's got his own catchphrase,
"I'm taking out the trash
and sorting it."

304
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:50,041
And this guy, this guy,
he grew up in the bayou,

305
00:15:50,041 --> 00:15:53,291
living with alligators,
wrestling with alligators.

306
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:56,083
I call him The Aviator.

307
00:15:56,083 --> 00:16:00,875
Fight night's already sold-out.
I set up a ring.
Fans can make bets.

308
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:03,125
I even put out
some nice mixed nuts.

309
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:05,667
No!
Those are for people.

310
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:09,208
I can't believe
you muscled out your own son.
You stink, Dad.

311
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:11,208
Oh, come on,
what's more important?

312
00:16:11,208 --> 00:16:13,834
Your hopes and dreams
or me making more
than your mother?

313
00:16:13,834 --> 00:16:17,333
-This is pure exploitation.
I'm gonna tell Mom.
-Go ahead.

314
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,500
Then your homeless pals
will be right back
on the street,

315
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,625
where the nights are cold
and the fights are meatless.

316
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:24,125
This isn't over.

317
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,542
Yeah, it's been
that kind of week,
girlfriend,

318
00:16:28,542 --> 00:16:31,000
but, uh, hey,
T.G.I. hump day, huh?

319
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,959
Roger, who are you
talking to?

320
00:16:32,959 --> 00:16:35,625
Tammy, down at Mencer Escrow.
We're phone buddies.

321
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:38,792
Did you copy
those title reports?

322
00:16:38,792 --> 00:16:43,583
Tams, I gotta go.
Yeah, the boss is being
a real "Catch 'U' Next Tuesday."

323
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:45,792
Stan the Man is back.
Here you go.

324
00:16:45,792 --> 00:16:48,250
Just my little way
of saying you can keep
your little job.

325
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:51,542
-A diamond ring!
-I also got you a mink stole.

326
00:16:51,542 --> 00:16:54,917
Oh, my God!
But, Stan,
can we afford this?

327
00:16:54,917 --> 00:16:57,166
Well, you can't,
but I can.

328
00:16:57,166 --> 00:16:59,583
-But how did you get--
-Shh. Smile for LeRoy Neiman.

329
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:02,625
-He's painting us right now.
-That's LeRoy Neiman?

330
00:17:02,625 --> 00:17:05,667
I know, I thought
he was black too.

331
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:08,667
I've gotta
hand it to you, Dad.
You really pulled it off.

332
00:17:08,667 --> 00:17:10,667
Or did you?

333
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:16,000
You unionized
the homeless?

334
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,750
Yep. This is
the Fighting Bums Local 302.

335
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:22,834
ALL: Yeah!

336
00:17:22,834 --> 00:17:25,041
Here are our demands.

337
00:17:25,041 --> 00:17:28,375
"Longer red lights
at freeway off-ramps.
Free doggy day care.

338
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:31,041
Human dignity"?
I can't meet these demands.

339
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:33,083
Then you better
start refunding
everyone's money,

340
00:17:33,083 --> 00:17:35,083
'cause there won't be
any bum fights tonight.

341
00:17:35,083 --> 00:17:37,750
-No! You can't take my money.
-Don't sweat it, Dad.

342
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:40,125
I found a bum
who's willing to scab.

343
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:42,500
Now all you gotta do
is dress up like a bum
and fight him.

344
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,834
Son, you're a lifesaver.

345
00:17:44,834 --> 00:17:48,792
All right, where's the bum
who's stupid enough
to step into a ring with me?

346
00:17:48,792 --> 00:17:51,500
-(growls)
-Who the hell is that?

347
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:53,667
-He doesn't have a name.
-What do you mean?

348
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:56,583
He killed his own name.

349
00:17:57,709 --> 00:17:59,667
Ptooey!
(laughs)

350
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:02,625
My God, Steve!
You couldn't get me
The Aviator

351
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:04,875
or The Tickler
or Pillow Hands McGraw?

352
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:08,333
No way! Not me!
I ain't no scab!

353
00:18:09,959 --> 00:18:12,500
Dad, this is suicide.
You're a weapons expert.

354
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:15,041
When was the last time
you fought hand-to-hand?

355
00:18:15,041 --> 00:18:17,583
I'll be fine, Hayley.
You never forget how to fight.

356
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:19,959
-It's like beating up a bicycle.
-(bell dings)

357
00:18:21,917 --> 00:18:24,125
-(bones crack, groans)
-(growls)

358
00:18:24,125 --> 00:18:26,417
Don't let it eat my heart.

359
00:18:28,083 --> 00:18:30,750
(yells, grunts)

360
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:32,959
(laughs)

361
00:18:32,959 --> 00:18:35,083
This is a wonderful
starter home.

362
00:18:35,083 --> 00:18:37,583
I've been saving it
for a couple just like you.

363
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:40,041
Pretty soon we're gonna
be more than a couple.

364
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:43,166
Oh, congratulations.
I just thought you were fat.

365
00:18:43,166 --> 00:18:47,291
-We're adopting.
-Let me show you the backyard.

366
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:49,583
It's the perfect place
for a baby to play.

367
00:18:49,583 --> 00:18:52,875
-(crowd cheers)
-(screams) Oh, my God!

368
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:55,542
Stop it!
Stan, what are you doing?

369
00:18:55,542 --> 00:18:57,709
Leave my husband alone.

370
00:18:57,709 --> 00:19:01,834
-Look, that bum's wife has to
jump in and save him.
-What a wuss.

371
00:19:01,834 --> 00:19:05,250
(all laughing)

372
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:18,834
(crowd gasps)
Oh?

373
00:19:18,834 --> 00:19:21,458
It's a knockout.
My dad wins!

374
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:24,500
I lost a pile of dough
on that one-thumb psycho.

375
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:27,417
Me too.
Let's exit quickly.

376
00:19:27,417 --> 00:19:30,166
I did it.
I'm Stan the Man.

377
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:33,250
-Not really.
-We paid this guy
to take a dive.

378
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:37,166
-Then bet everything on you.
-This whole thing was a setup?

379
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:41,208
More of a performance piece.
Hi. Ted Fiedler, method actor.

380
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:43,250
I'm also a hand model.

381
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:47,041
(laughs, gasps)
No!

382
00:19:47,041 --> 00:19:50,291
-Stan, why did you do this?
-Oh, money.

383
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:53,166
You make more of it than me.
I'm a failure as a man.

384
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:55,959
You big dope.
Don't you get it?
We're a team.

385
00:19:55,959 --> 00:19:58,000
I know, and you're the owner.
I get it.

386
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,500
No, Stan, we're equals.

387
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:03,083
We share everything,
good and bad.

388
00:20:03,083 --> 00:20:05,333
You don't have to feel
threatened by my job.

389
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:08,792
So, you mean,
when you succeed,
I succeed.

390
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:11,208
Exactly.

391
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:14,000
Hey, I was gonna
hitch a ride home,
but I bit my thumb off.

392
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,750
-So use your other one.
-Right. Thanks.

393
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:18,834
Hey, teach a man
to fish, huh?

394
00:20:23,959 --> 00:20:26,000
I made you fresh coffee.

395
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:29,125
-Have a good day
at work, partner.
-Shh!

396
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:31,834
Interest rates
went up this morning
by a whopping 20 points,

397
00:20:31,834 --> 00:20:34,041
sending mortgage rates
soaring.

398
00:20:34,041 --> 00:20:36,500
Uh, smart play
locking us in on
that low fixed rate, Terry.

399
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:39,166
-Thank you.
-Said the man who is finally
learning his own self-worth.

400
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:42,250
This senseless rate hike
by Federal Reserve Chairman
Alan Greenspan

401
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,583
has jeopardized
the fragile U.S. economy

402
00:20:44,583 --> 00:20:47,041
and put every real estate agent
in the country out of work.

403
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:49,208
That's a shame.
I'm sorry, hon.

404
00:20:49,208 --> 00:20:52,834
Can I keep this mouse pad?
I'm keeping this mouse pad.

405
00:20:52,834 --> 00:20:55,083
Oh, well, at least
I had some fun,

406
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:57,959
and you learned there's no need
to be threatened by my success.

407
00:20:57,959 --> 00:21:00,709
Absolutely.
Go, Team Smith.

408
00:21:02,875 --> 00:21:05,375
It's Stan the Man.
Release Greenspan's schnauzer.

409
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:08,333
Fannie Mae!
(groans)

410
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:10,959
That's all for
the morning report.
We'll see you at noon.

411
00:21:10,959 --> 00:21:12,959
-(whistling tune)
-GREG: And I'll
see you tonight.

412
00:21:12,959 --> 00:21:14,875
-Greg!
-Oh, relax. Everybody knows.

413
00:21:55,834 --> 00:21:57,750
Bye-bye.
See you soon.

